        last_assistant_message: "**Phase 1 is complete!** Here's a summary of everything built:\n\n## Phase 1: Complete\n\n### 7 Steps Completed\n\n| Step | Component | Tests | Status |\n|------|-----------|-------|--------|\n| 1 | Proto contract (`plugin.proto`) | buf lint + go build | Done |\n| 2 | Plugin SDK (`libs/go/`) | 11 tests | Done |\n| 3 | Orchestrator (`services/orchestrator/`) | 10 tests | Done |\n| 4 | storage.markdown plugin | 11 tests | Done |\n| 5 | tools.features plugin (34 tools) | 24 tests | Done |\n| 6 | transport.stdio plugin (MCP bridge) | 20 tests | Done |\n| 7 | Wire together (go.work, Makefile, e2e) | 7-step E2E | Done |\n\n### 4 Binaries\n- `bin/orchestrator` — Central hub, starts plugins, routes QUIC messages\n- `bin/storage-markdown` — Disk storage (META + Markdown format)\n- `bin/tools-features` — 34 feature workflow tools\n- `bin/transport-stdio` — MCP JSON-RPC stdin/stdout bridge\n\n### End-to-End Flow Verified\n```\nAgent → transport.stdio (JSON-RPC stdin) \n      → orchestrator (QUIC routing)\n      → tools.features (create_feature)\n      → orchestrator (StorageWrite proxy)\n      → storage.markdown (disk write)\n      → FEAT-XXX.md appears on disk with META block\n```\n\n### Bug Fixes During Wiring\n1. **Plugin READY address** — Plugins printed `READY localhost:0` instead of actual address. Fixed with `Server.ActualAddr()` that blocks until bind.\n2. **Storage route registration** — Orchestrator didn't know storage.markdown provides \"markdown\" storage. Fixed by adding `provides_storage` to config YAML.\n\n### Commands\n```bash\nmake build       # Build all 4 binaries\nmake test        # Run 66 unit tests\nmake test-e2e    # Full integration test\n```"
