        last_assistant_message: |-
            Looking at what we have and what would deliver the most value quickly, here are the small wins ranked by impact:

            **1. Git commit + push** — All this work is uncommitted. One command and it's safe.

            **2. `orchestra-mcp init`** — A bootstrap command so any project can run `orchestra-mcp init` and get a working `.mcp.json`, `plugins.yaml`, `CLAUDE.md`, etc. This makes the system immediately usable by AI agents in any repo.

            **3. `make dev`** — A single command that starts orchestrator + plugins with hot-reload (`air` or similar), so you can develop against a live system.

            **4. Plugin auto-discovery** — Instead of declaring `provides_storage` in YAML, have the plugin send its full manifest during registration. Removes manual config duplication.

            **5. `transport.sse`** — An SSE/HTTP transport plugin so the web dashboard can connect (not just stdin/stdout).

            The fastest, highest-value win is **#1** (commit) followed by **#2** (init command) since it makes the whole system usable. Which one would you like to start with?
